SUMMARY:Housing Biweekly Meeting
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the March 16 meeting of the Housing Justice Working Group! Free food and drinks will be provided. \nThe Housing Justice Working Group is committed to creating a Seattle without sweeps\, evictions\, or housing scarcity\, where housing is a human right and not a commodity. \nOur agenda is available on Seattle DSA’s Discord in the housing-justice-general channel (see the pinned message). If you’re a member of Seattle DSA and haven’t joined the Discord yet\, please do so here.
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/housing-biweekly-meeting-6/
LOCATION:Cathy Hildebrand Community Room\, 923 E John St\, Seattle\, Washington\, 98102\, United States
CATEGORIES:Housing,New Member Friendly
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://seattledsa.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/sdsa_housing_justice_working_group.png
END:VEVENT
